{
  "text": "Treatment of the cell lines with 5-aza-dC can induce genes without a direct consequence of CpG island demethylation [CITATION_1] . We examined the methylation status in two putative genes by MSP and one of them, GADD45B, was not methylated in any of the 15 CRC cell lines (Table II, Fig. 3A) . In addition to the up-regulation of two genes with no CpG islands, up-regulation of such genes might be a secondary effect caused by an induced upstream factor (e.g. genes in the p53 DNA damage pathway) [CITATION_2] .",
